Gemini: OPEN WINDOWS EXPLORER (File Explorer).

NAVIGATE to the FOLDER where your ai_system.py WAS located. This is the folder where you've been working on your AI system code (likely C:\AI-Execution-System).

LOOK CAREFULLY in that folder. Do you see a file named main.py?

IS THERE A FILE NAMED main.py VISIBLE IN THAT FOLDER? (Yes/No)
DOUBLE-CHECK THE FILE EXTENSION: Make sure it's .py and not something like main.py.txt or just main (with no extension). If you have file extensions hidden in Windows, you might need to enable viewing file extensions to be 100% sure it's .py.
ALSO, CHECK if there is STILL a file named ai_system.py in that folder.

IS THERE STILL A FILE NAMED ai_system.py IN THAT FOLDER? (Yes/No)
REPORT BACK EXACTLY WHAT YOU SEE IN WINDOWS EXPLORER in that folder:

"YES, I SEE main.py in the folder." AND "NO, I do NOT see ai_system.py anymore."
"NO, I do NOT see main.py in the folder." AND "YES, I DO still see ai_system.py."
"I see BOTH main.py AND ai_system.py in the folder."
Something else (describe what you see).
WE NEED TO BE 100% SURE THAT ai_system.py IS RENAMED TO main.py IN THE FILE SYSTEM before we proceed.

PLEASE CAREFULLY CHECK YOUR FILE SYSTEM and REPORT BACK WHAT YOU SEE! Let's get this file naming issue sorted out so we can get to the cloud deployment! GO! GO! GO!
